      <description>&lt;p&gt;This is walk through in APB specification &lt;code&gt;AMBA 3 APB Protocol&lt;/code&gt;. The spec is short but i thought to document my notes anyway.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;introduction&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Introduction&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;heading-link&#34; href=&#34;#introduction&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;i class=&#34;fa-solid fa-link&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; title=&#34;Link to heading&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&#xA;    &lt;span class=&#34;sr-only&#34;&gt;Link to heading&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;APB is AMBA low-speed bus that provide basic write/read transfer. no pipelines with minimum access time of 2 cycles.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;transfers&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Transfers&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;heading-link&#34; href=&#34;#transfers&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;i class=&#34;fa-solid fa-link&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; title=&#34;Link to heading&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&#xA;    &lt;span class=&#34;sr-only&#34;&gt;Link to heading&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Chapter 2 explains  write and read transfer with 2 variants&lt;/p&gt;</description>
